description:
When I was a young boy (1950's), I learned to play golf by closely watching the best players at the course I grew up on. I would then stand in front of a window and copy their swings... then I would go to the practice area to ingrain that look and new feeling to muscle memory. That WAS and STILL IS a great way to learn! It's called SELF-DISCOVERY! 

When you discover a helpful motion or thought ALL BY YOURSELF, YOU WILL NEVER FORGET IT! - I never have!  

At the age of 78, I'm still a mid single-digit player. My goal with this YouTube channel is to provide a platform for TEACHING and LEARNING! I will provide videos and detailed descriptions of the finest golfers in the world, their swings and some of their finest shots so YOU can learn and improve as I have. 

The focus here is geared toward TEACHING and LEARNING the short game (putting, chipping, pitching and wedge play from 120-yards in), but you will also see some of the finest, Tour-Proven full swings and descriptions as well.⛳️

My name is Pete and I complete video games. Are you looking for that Walkthrough that uncovers every last hidden secret of a game? Want to see a Let’s Play without someone failing over and over again while you are holding yourself back from punching through the screen? I got you covered! 

Consider me the absolute opposite of a ‘blind’ let’s player. As a completionist, I think that you as the viewer should never have to experience the feeling that you missed out on something in the game. Completing games can be tedious, therefore I put a lot of planning into each game to make even grabbing collectibles fit into the storyline and make the gameplay look as entertaining as possible. 

Pete Complete – that means completion in every aspect, high quality and entertainment. I want to be the very best I can be, so you can have a great time. Leave a comment or subscribe if you like my videos, it really helps me out.

Cheers,

Pete

Tech Tips, Honest Reviews, and Useful Tutorials!

I'm Jerad Hill, a Husband, Father of 4, Entrepreneur (Since 2000), YouTuber, Photographer, and Pilot. Follow along as I share my technological journey through stories, opinions, and reviews. 

I have enjoyed sharing my love of Tech with others since I was a child. I’m a digital marketer, husband, father, and pilot living in Northwestern Montana.

In 2008, I started a podcast called The iPhone App Podcast, reviewing iPhone Apps. I changed the name to Daily App Show and expanded to Android reviews as well. A few years later, State of Tech was born out of a desire to discuss a broader range of tech and how we use it in our lives. Fast forward a decade, and I’ve decided to rebrand this channel to my own name. I share my tech journey and experiences here, which makes more sense to be my name. 

I hope you choose to come along by subscribing to this channel and signing up for my free email newsletter.

I really love sharing music and that's what I do on the channel in a form of 'thematic' music compilations. The best words that can describe the music I prefer are: Melodic, Progressive, Emotion-heavy, Powerful, Cinematic. I found those qualities to be represented the most in Mainstream Drum & Bass and Melodic Dubstep, which is also the majority of music I upload to the channel.

The key thing I wanted to have in my own compilations, that I lacked in most existing ones, is very specific 'theme' of the music in each of them, characterizing the general mood and specific qualities of the tracks.

Don't wanna wait for the next compilation and have all the music RIGHT NOW? Here is the full list of the tracks that I like and constantly update: https://goo.gl/fstKbM. Please let me know if you were able to use it in any way!

Welcome to the Pecos Hank Channel... Nature with a twist! 
Here you'll find the most beautiful collection of storm footage in existence. Tornadoes, lightning, supercells and all facets of severe thunderstorms are presented in cinematic and educational fashion.

Hank's footage airs worldwide and clients include BBC Earth, Nat Geo, Disney, TWC, CNN, Discovery and many more. Look for Hank's storm footage in the major motion picture "The Last Witch Hunter," "Supercell," and Netflix original "TAU" as well as BBC's "Seven Worlds." 

About Pecos Hank:
Half musician, half filmmaker documenting severe weather since 1994,  Hank witnessed his first tornadoes in 2002.  In 2013 he documented the widest tornado ever, in 2014 the fastest-moving tornado ever and in 2019 discovered a new TLE called a green ghost.  Almost all the music in these videos was composed by Pecos Hank.

description:
I'm 27. May 13th 2014 I sat at home thinking to myself about how much I love skateboarding and how it has a huge part in my life. As I sat there I reached a decision. The decision to share my skateboarding with the world. To start a youtube channel and put my skateboarding on the internet for the world to see. Now here I am, with over 100 public videos, 2 Top google result videos, and thousands of views. I love that grey button at the top of youtube that reads "upload" because everytime I click it I get genuinely excited to be able to share some more of the sport I love so much with the world. I'm just a canadian who loves to have a skateboard under his feet. I'm just a canadian who loves to show the world my love for the sport through youtube videos. Thank you to every fan. Thank you to every person who has ever clicked on, shared, likes, favorited, or watched my videos. I do this for you guys.

description: We are Dave and Karen Beightol.  We live in one of the most historic areas of Colorado, at about 8500 feet in the rocky mountains. Central City, CO. to be exact. We have spent most of our lives as professional photographers, computer gurus, and web site designers. We came to Colorado from Indiana in 2000 to expand our photography skills and business. We found it a very tight, local market here at that time. We moved on into computer and web services, where we made a good living for many years. We now own and operate the only all natural restaurant on the mountain. Burger Joint. Nothing from a box, can or microwave, is our motto. After semi retiring into the natural food business, we have decided to get back to our love of images. With our computer and technical background, combined with our photo and video skills, we though that areal imaging via UAV drones would be a perfect fit. Add this to a geographically spectacular location and here we are. NOW FCC LICENSED!
